    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">Activities</div>
      <div class="card-content">
        <ul>
          <li>Activity 1: Organizing Quran, ethics, beliefs, and jurisprudence classes throughout the year.</li>
          <li>Activity 2: Holding gatherings and exhibitions, conducting environmental advertising, creating a messaging system, designing and launching a website and blog, and executing religious dialogues.</li>
          <li>Activity 3: Conducting cultural and religious activities, including preparing, editing, and facilitating the publication and distribution of books, CDs, publications, and religious brochures, and using modern advertising methods like social networks and virtual chat rooms.</li>
          <li>Activity 4: Organizing cultural activities during religious and revolutionary occasions such as Fatimiyyah Days, I'tikaf, Unity Week, the Ten Days of Dignity, Mid-Sha'ban, Ghadir Khum, Muharram and Safar, Ramadan, Women's Day, Nowruz, Teacher's Day, the anniversary of Imam Khomeini's passing, the 15th of Khordad, the anniversary of 9th of Dey, the Ten Days of Fajr, and the days of sacrifice and martyrdom.</li>
          <li>Activity 5: Organizing training courses in family and Islamic lifestyle, religious upbringing, child and adolescent education, proper upbringing of children and adolescents, interaction with children and adolescents, child and adolescent guidance and counseling, life skills training, family interaction, personality analysis, crisis management, identifying age-related problems in childhood and adolescence, and methods for solving problems and challenges faced by children and adolescents, crisis management, anger management, stress management, emotional management, financial management, self-awareness, talent growth, identifying children's and adolescents' talents, talent-based upbringing and talent assessment, spousal skills, effective communication skills, marriage skills, and pre-marriage skills.</li>
        </ul>
